    Networking: Knowledge of network protocols, routing, switching, and troubleshooting network issues.

    Operating Systems: Proficiency in operating systems such as Windows, Linux, or macOS, including installation, configuration, and troubleshooting.

    System Administration: Ability to manage and administer servers, including user management, backup and recovery, and system performance optimization.

    Virtualization: Understanding of virtualization technologies such as VMware or Hyper-V to create and manage virtual machines.

    Cloud Computing: Knowledge of cloud platforms like Amazon Web Services (AWS), Microsoft Azure, or Google Cloud Platform, including cloud architecture and service deployment.

    Database Management: Proficiency in database management systems such as MySQL, Oracle, or Microsoft SQL Server, including database design, querying, and optimization.

    IT Security: Understanding of security principles and best practices, including access control, encryption, vulnerability management, and security incident response.

    Scripting and Automation: Ability to write scripts (e.g., PowerShell, Bash, Python) to automate routine tasks and streamline IT operations.

    IT Service Management (ITSM): Familiarity with ITSM frameworks such as ITIL, including incident management, change management, and service desk processes.

    Troubleshooting and Problem Solving: Strong analytical and problem-solving skills to diagnose and resolve technical issues.

    Hardware and Software Installation: Knowledge of hardware components and software installation processes for servers, workstations, and network devices.

    Backup and Recovery: Understanding of backup strategies, data recovery methods, and disaster recovery planning.

    Network Security: Proficiency in implementing and managing network security measures such as firewalls, VPNs, and intrusion detection systems.

    Cybersecurity Awareness: Familiarity with common cybersecurity threats, best practices, and techniques to protect against cyber attacks.

    IT Project Management: Ability to plan, coordinate, and manage IT projects, including resource allocation, timelines, and deliverables.

    Mobile Device Management: Knowledge of mobile device management (MDM) solutions and policies for secure device configuration and management.

    IT Governance: Understanding of IT governance frameworks and practices to ensure alignment with business objectives and compliance with regulations.

    Disaster Recovery Planning: Proficiency in developing and implementing disaster recovery plans to minimize downtime and data loss in case of disruptions.

    Change Management: Ability to manage and implement changes to IT systems and infrastructure while minimizing disruptions to operations.

    IT Infrastructure Monitoring: Knowledge of monitoring tools and techniques to track system performance, identify bottlenecks, and proactively resolve issues.

    Data Center Management: Understanding of data center operations, including server rack management, power distribution, and cooling systems.

    IT Asset Management: Proficiency in managing IT assets, including hardware and software inventory, license tracking, and asset lifecycle management.

    IT Compliance: Knowledge of regulatory compliance requirements (e.g., GDPR, HIPAA, PCI DSS) and the ability to ensure adherence to security and privacy standards.

    Network Administration: Ability to configure and manage network devices, IP addressing, DNS, DHCP, and network troubleshooting.

    Collaboration Tools: Familiarity with collaboration platforms such as Microsoft Teams or Slack for effective communication and teamwork.

    Data Backup and Storage: Understanding of data backup strategies, storage technologies, and data deduplication techniques.

    Remote Desktop Support: Ability to provide remote technical support to end-users, troubleshoot issues, and perform system maintenance.

    IT Documentation: Proficiency in creating and maintaining technical documentation, including system configurations, procedures, and user guides.

    IT Asset Security: Knowledge of asset security controls, including physical security, data encryption, and secure disposal of assets.

    Customer Service: Strong interpersonal and communication skills to provide excellent customer service and support to end-users.